A former Executive Secretary of the National Human Rights Commission (NHRC), Prof. Bem Anweh, was shot in the leg yesterday by unknown gunmen in Gboko metropolis of Gboko Local Government Area in Benue State. Daily Trust on Sunday learnt that the incident occurred around 10am, at a petrol station near Gyado suburb in Gboko. The Police Public Relations Officer of the Benue Command (PPRO), DSP Catherine Anene, confirmed the incident but added that the police were yet to get details of what transpired at the time of filing this report. However, locals told our correspondent that the gunmen caused panic at the scene of the operation as they shot sporadically into the air. It was further gathered that the gunmen left the scene immediately after carrying out the attack on Anweh, who was immediately taken to a hospital in Gboko, and later moved to the Benue State University Teaching Hospital in Makurdi. Gunmen shoots ex-NHRC boss in Benue Police investigate Gboko  killings Gunmen kill 3 in Benue